<dl id="n41055e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41055e">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41055e"> 55(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> oriented</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Since the Lord as a sun is constantly in the east, therefore the ancients, with whom all things of worship were representative of spiritual things, turned their faces <mark>to the east</mark> in their adorations; and that they might do the like in all worship, they also turned their temples thither: from which churches of the present day are built with this direction. <small> Emanuel Swedenborg, <a name="ESAW" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ESAW"><cite title="source">Angelic Wisdom Concerning the Divine Love</cite></a> (ed. unknown) 123</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
